7.3 BHA - SHAREHOLDER'S CORPORATE MAINTENANCE MATTERS FOR 2026

The General Manager Planning and Development and the Deputy Chief Administrative Officer/Chief Financial Officer submitted a report seeking Council approval with respect to certain annual shareholder’s corporate maintenance matters for 2026 on behalf of the Burnaby Housing Authority Corporation (BHA).
MOVED AND SECONDED
Resolution No. 2026 - 167
THAT the City, as outlined in the report titled “BHA – Shareholder’s Corporate Maintenance Matters for 2026”, dated April 14, 2026, as sole shareholder of the Burnaby Housing Authority Corporation (BHA): and;
• authorize the business of the annual general meeting of the BHA for the 2026 year to be transacted through an unanimous shareholders resolution;
• select December 12, 2026 as the annual reference date for the BHA;
• appoint KPMG as auditor of the BHA until the next annual general meeting of the BHA, and the directors of the BHA be authorized to determine the remuneration payable to the auditor, and to give the auditor notice of appointment as required by the Business Corporations Act (British Columbia);
• receive the BHA’s financial statements for the period ending December 31, 2025; and
• appoint the individuals identified in section 3.3 as directors of the BHA in accordance with the terms set out in section.
THAT the Shareholder Representative be directed to execute such shareholders resolutions as necessary to give effect to the foregoing resolutions.
CARRIED UNANIMOUSLY

